ngly important role of other people within our lived experience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aOther (Philosophy) 0aOther (Philosophy). 0aPerception (Philosophy) 0aPerception (Philosophy). 0aPhenomenology. 4aEducation : Early Childhood Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847173040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438471730423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438471730/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles